> Full quality gates reference is in `docs/atdd/quality-gates.md`.

## Available Gates

Detect which gates the project supports from its configuration files:

1. **Lint** — ESLint, Biome, Ruff, Flake8, RuboCop, golangci-lint, Clippy
2. **Format** — Prettier, Biome, Black, Ruff format, rustfmt, gofmt
3. **Type check** — TypeScript, mypy, pyright, .NET, Go
4. **Build** — npm build, dotnet build, go build, cargo build, make, gradle, maven
5. **Test** — Full test suite (mandatory gate)

## When to Run

- After all scenarios are implemented (before refactor)
- After refactoring is complete
- Before creating a PR

## Execution Rules

- Auto-fix lint and format issues when the tool supports it
- Fix type errors and build failures in production code, never in tests
- Run all gates and iterate until they pass (max 3 attempts per gate)
- If a gate still fails after 3 attempts, escalate to the user
- After fixing any gate, re-run ALL gates to catch regressions
